3. Scope & Applicability

This Policy applies to personal data collected through the Pomorix mobile application on devices running supported operating systems, and to services, support and communications associated with the App.

4. Information We Collect

We only collect the data necessary to operate, maintain and improve the App. Types of information we collect:

4.1 Personal data you provide directly

Email address when you contact support or provide feedback.

Feedback, support messages and other text you submit via in-App forms or email.

Any optional information you choose to submit (e.g., when you fill an optional form).

4.2 Device & usage data (automatic)

Device identifiers and technical data (device model, OS version, app version, package name, build id).

Usage and analytics data (number and length of sessions, feature usage, screens visited).

Crash reports, error logs and diagnostic data.

Local settings saved on your device (preferred language, theme, timer settings). These are typically stored locally on your device.

4.3 Local media and assets

The App includes packaged background music and sound assets. We do not access your personal photos, audio or other media unless you explicitly enable a feature that requests such access; if and when we add such a feature you will be prompted for permission separately.

4.4 What we don’t collect by default

Pomorix does not require an account to use core features. We do not collect names, postal addresses or sensitive personal data (such as financial information, health data, racial or religious information) by default.

5. How We Use Your Data (Purposes & Legal Basis)

We process personal data to support the App and your use of it. Purposes include:

Operating, providing and maintaining the App and its features (necessary for performance of our services).

Analyzing and improving the App, including analytics and crash reporting (legitimate interest in improving our product).

Responding to feedback and support requests (to fulfill user requests).

Sending service messages or notifications where you have given required consent.

Complying with legal obligations and enforcing our rights.

Where the law requires consent (for example, certain push notification or marketing permissions), we will obtain that consent and you may withdraw it at any time without affecting prior processing.

6. Third-Party Services & Sharing

We use third-party service providers to host, operate and analyse the App (for example, analytics, crash reporting, cloud messaging and distribution). These providers process data on our behalf under contract and only to the extent necessary to provide their services.

Examples include services provided by Google LLC (e.g., Firebase services, Google Play distribution) and the Apple App Store (distribution). We may also use third-party SDKs for in-app reviews, updates, or audio playback. We do not sell your personal data.

We may disclose personal data: (a) to processors who help deliver the App; (b) to comply with laws, government requests, court orders or to protect the rights, property or safety of Pomorix or others; and (c) at your request (for example, to export or erase data you ask us to remove). Third-party providers may process or store data outside India; see Section 7.

Relevant provider terms (e.g., Firebase, Play Store, App Store) govern how those services handle data.

7. Cross-Border Data Transfers & Safeguards

Your device and usage data may be processed or stored in countries outside India (for instance on cloud infrastructure or third-party provider servers). Where data is transferred across borders we put appropriate contractual safeguards in place and rely on legal mechanisms available under applicable law to protect your personal data.

8. Data Retention

We retain personal data only as long as needed to provide the App and fulfil the purposes in this Policy, or as required by law. Typical retention practices:

Support requests and feedback: retained until the request is resolved and for a reasonable period afterward unless you request deletion earlier.

Analytics and crash logs: retained in aggregated or pseudonymised form for product improvement; specific retention periods vary by provider and are typically limited (for example, months).

Local settings: stored on your device until you uninstall the App or reset settings.

If you request deletion, we will erase your personal data from our systems and instruct processors to do the same, subject to any legal obligations to retain certain records.

9. Security

We maintain reasonable administrative, technical and physical safeguards to protect personal data against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration or destruction (for example, access controls, HTTPS for data in transit, and contractual protections with vendors). No system can be guaranteed 100% secure; in the event of a data breach we will follow applicable notification requirements and applicable law.

10. Children’s Privacy

The App is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe we have collected personal data from a child under 13, please contact us at pomorixapp@gmail.com
 and we will promptly delete the data.

11. Your Rights & How to Exercise Them

Under applicable Indian law and DPDP principles you may have rights including: access, correction, erasure (deletion), and withdrawal of consent. You may also nominate someone to act on your behalf where permitted.

To submit a request, email pomorixapp@gmail.com
 with the subject line “Privacy Request” and include: (a) your name; (b) the email address associated with the request (or a clear description of your device/app identifiers); and (c) a clear description of the request (access / correction / deletion / portability / withdrawal of consent). We will verify your identity and respond within the timeframe required by applicable law. Where permitted by law, you may escalate unresolved complaints to the Data Protection Board or relevant authority.

